					<div class="content content-links" data-slug="panel1" data-section-content>
					<h6>Beginners and More Experienced categories</h6>
					<p>Since 2012, EAC Art Awards have introduced a dual judging and prize structure, with separate beginner and more experienced/semi-professional artist categories. The separation of these two groups has helped to widen the appeal of The Awards, and to celebrate the quality of work and the talents of both.</p>
					<h6>Judging and Selection of prize-winners and highly commended artists</h6>
					<p>The judging panel, composed of art professionals and sponsors, makes a selection of prize-winners and highly commended artists from the online gallery of submitted images. Within four weeks of the closing date for entries, successful entrants are informed and subsequently invited to a celebration and prize-giving afternoon event at an iconic venue – in 2012/13 The House of Lords. Successful entrants do not need to transport their original work to the venue – prize-winning entries are displayed on large TV screens.</p>
					</div>
				</section>
