					<p class="title" data-section-title><a href="#panel2">Prizes</a></p>
					<div class="content" data-slug="panel2" data-section-content>
					<h6>Prizes</h6>
					<p>Two prizes of £125 each will be awarded in each category, one for the best entry from a beginner and the other for the best entry from a more experienced artist. All artists must choose an appropriate category for each submission, from the following:</p>
					<div class="row">
						<div class="small-12 large-8 columns">
							<p>Watercolour<br>Oil<br>Drawing<br>Still life<br>Portrait<br>Landscape / Seascape<br>3D work – sculpture / craft / textile<br>Photography / Digital Art</p>
						</div>
						<div class="small-12 large-4 columns">
							<a href="#"><img src="assets/img/prizes-hilary-dancer.jpg" class="hero-image" data-reveal-id="heroInfoSun" alt="Into the Sun by Hilary Dancer, Highly Commended 2012"></a>
							<p><small>'Into the Sun' by Hilary Dancer, Highly Commended 2012</small></p>	
						</div>
					</div>
					<h6>The Angela Farnell Memorial Prize</h6>
					<p>Two £500 prizes will be awarded in memory of the founder of EAC. These prizes will be for the best entries from artists living in sheltered / retirement housing or a care home, or who entered through a day centre. The prize-money is divided between the artist and their sheltered scheme, care home or day centre.</p>
					<h6>The Art & Wellbeing Prize</h6>
					<p>One prize of £250 will be awarded. This is an optional prize for those who wish to share their experience of how their involvement in artistic activities has had a positive affect on their recovery from illness or a life-changing event. Individuals can either enter themselves for this prize or can be nominated by an art group leader, care home manager, health professional, or family and friends. Entries for this Prize are judged on the submitted image along with a short statement. Statements from last year will be considered if they are re-submitted with a brief update note.</p>
					<h6>Prize for Group Work</h6>
					<p>One prize of £250 will be awarded to the best collaborative entry.</p>
					<h6>The People's Choice Awards</h6>
					<p>Three People’s Choice prizes will be awarded in 2014. The overall winner will receive £150, and two runners up will each receive £75. Visitors to the online gallery vote for the People's Choice Award, with voting opening once the deadline for entries has passed.</p>
