					<h6>The EAC People’s Choice Award</h6>
					<div class="row update-margin">
						<div class="small-12 large-8 columns">
							<p>Voting for the popular EAC People’s Choice Award takes place once all the entries are in and the images available to view online – generally within one week of the closing date.</p>
					<p>The People’s Choice Award is a popular and exciting aspect of the Art Awards competition. Artists, their family and friends, and the general public can become involved by voting online for their three favourite works of art. Anyone can vote, whatever their age; after an initial registration, voters are allocated three rosettes to attach to their 1st, 2nd and 3rd preferences. </p>
						</div>
						<div class="small-12 large-4 columns">
							<a href="#"><img src="assets/img/harry-hero.jpg" class="hero-image" data-reveal-id="heroInfoHarry" alt="Harry by Edward Clark, entrant 2012"></a>
							<p class="text-center"><small>'Harry' by Edward Clark, entrant 2012</small></p>	
						</div>
					</div>
					<p>Voters have approx 4 weeks to browse the gallery and cast their votes. Voters can change their mind and de-select and re-select alternative preferences.  Comments can also be added, which are very much appreciated by entrants. Positive and constructive criticism are very much encouraged but please note that all comments are moderated before being posted on the artists’ page.</p>
